benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/catalog/xml - Upload the full catalog as XML

covered: Valid POST payloads with correct headers across multiple scenarios (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC11, TC13)
Invalid/malformed payloads and input validation (malformed XML, empty body, whitespace-only XML, corrupted payload, invalid encoding)
Header/validation scenarios (missing required header, empty header, invalid content-type)
Service unavailability and server error handling (503) via backend down scenario (TC16)
XML constructs and encoding support (whitespace, comments, CDATA, UTF-8/UTF-16)
gaps: Rate limiting / throttling behavior not tested
Explicit 409 handling for duplicate submissions not consistently validated
Internal server errors beyond 503 (e.g., DB failure) not tested
Authentication edge cases (e.g., expired tokens) not explicitly covered
recommendations: Add rate limiting tests to verify throttling and graceful degradation under high load
Add tests verifying caching behavior (ETag, Cache-Control) and cache invalidation on updates
Clarify and validate duplicate submission behavior with explicit 409 response where applicable
Introduce 500-level error scenarios (e.g., DB failures) to test server error handling beyond 503
Extend auth tests to cover token expiry/revocation scenarios and ensure consistent 401/403 handling across cases
